          "author": {
            "login": "ConcaveTrillion"
          },
          "body": "Filed from the pd-book-tools deep code/security review.\n\nReport: `docs/research/2026-05-22-deep-code-security-review.md`\nFinding: #32\n\nMoved from mistakenly filed meta issue: ConcaveTrillion/ocr-container-meta#325\n\nEvidence:\n\n- `pyproject.toml:2`\n- `pyproject.toml:18`\n- `.github/workflows/ci.yml:23`\n- `.github/workflows/ci.yml:25`\n\nBuild requirements and many runtime dependencies use broad lower bounds, and CI uses mutable action/tool references such as `astral-sh/setup-uv@v4` with `version: latest`.\n\nImpact:\n\n- Builds can change without reviewed repository diffs.\n\nRemediation:\n\n- Pin GitHub Actions to commit SHAs for release-critical workflows.\n- Pin `uv` versions.\n- Use lockfile/hash-enforced installs for releases.\n\n---\nThis issue was filed from a read-only review. Confirm behavior with a focused failing test before implementation where practical.",
          "closedAt": "2026-05-25T02:48:51Z",
          "comments": {
            "nodes": [
              {
                "author": {
                  "login": "ConcaveTrillion"
                },
                "body": "Fixed in commit 81a0a22: pinned actions/checkout and astral-sh/setup-uv to commit SHAs; pinned uv to 0.11.16.",
